{
  "text": "T cell effector function and tolerance are controlled through multiple signaling pathways regulated by interactions with antigen-presenting cells. T cell proliferation and effector function are positively regulated by various members of the B7 family interacting with costimulatory receptors as well as certain TNF family members and cytokines [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
